<paragraph id="8BAE36C88020BC54DFCAFE0D0A97FD12" blockId="2.[151,1436,393,706]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<taxonomicName id="4C114D4B8020BC54DFCAFE0D0864FE71" box="[151,328,393,417]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="facialis">
<emphasis id="B965EADA8020BC54DFCAFE0D0864FE71" box="[151,328,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Centris facialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus id="54AA886A8020BC54DE09FE0D0897FE72" box="[340,443,393,418]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">lectotype</typeStatus>
(♀, 
<figureCitation id="132A2A4D8020BC54DEAAFE0D0B4DFE71" box="[503,609,393,418]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1635,1658]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,758,1614]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,758,1614]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Lectotype (♀) Centris (Hemisiella) facialis Mocsáry, 1899: Fig. 1. Head, frontal view; Fig. 2. Habitus, lateral view; Fig. 3. Habitus, dorsal view; Fig. 4. Wing venation." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227848/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Figs 
<number id="3DD924EF8020BC54DD6EFE0D0B4DFE71" box="[563,609,393,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
</figureCitation>
): A single female labeled “ 
<collectingCountry id="F30676588020BC54DCF5FE0D0AD1FE72" box="[936,1021,393,418]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
/ S. Antonio”, “ 
<number id="3DD924EF8020BC54DB9BFE0D0DCAFE71" box="[1222,1254,393,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="93.0">93</number>
.” [green label], “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C114D4B8020BC54DFFEFE2909DAFE15" box="[163,246,429,453]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="facialis">
<emphasis id="B965EADA8020BC54DFFEFE2909DAFE15" box="[163,246,429,453]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">facialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ det. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B398020BC54DE1EFE2908E5FE16" author="Friese" box="[323,457,429,454]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" refString="Friese, H. (1898) Die Trigona - Arten Australiens. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 21, 427 - 431." type="journal article" year="1898">
Friese 
<number id="3DD924EF8020BC54DECCFE2A08E5FE16" box="[401,457,430,454]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1898.0">1898</number>
</bibRefCitation>
[printed] / Mocs.” is here designated as the 
<typeStatus id="54AA886A8020BC54DC93FE290D14FE16" box="[974,1080,429,454]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen agrees with the original description and is from the 
<typeStatus id="54AA886A8020BC54DD12FE560B53FE3A" box="[591,639,466,490]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">type</typeStatus>
locality (San Antonio, Potosí, 
<collectingCountry id="F30676588020BC54DCA6FE550D7EFE3A" box="[1019,1106,465,490]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
). Two additional specimens examined from 
<collectionCode id="ED00AE0D8020BC54DE16FE72088CFDDD" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" box="[331,416,502,525]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">HNHM</collectionCode>
were not from the 
<typeStatus id="54AA886A8020BC54DD23FE720BF9FDDE" box="[638,725,502,526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">syntype</typeStatus>
series, although 
<typeStatus id="54AA886A8020BC54DCCAFE720AC2FDDE" box="[919,1006,502,526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">syntype</typeStatus>
[now to be considered 
<typeStatus id="54AA886A8020BC54DBA1FE710CBAFDDE" box="[1276,1430,501,526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">paralectotype</typeStatus>
] specimens from “Songo” [Zongo, Cordillera Real, La Paz, 
<collectingCountry id="F30676588020BC54DC68FD9D0AA6FDE2" box="[821,906,537,562]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
] should exist in collections. The green colored label from this specimen, and the following material, simply indicates that the origin is within the Neotropical region. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B398020BC54DFB1FDE608E5FDAA" box="[236,457,609,634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell, 1901. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical region, Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba (Parana), pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B965EADA8020BC54DE63FDE6085CFDA9" box="[318,368,609,633]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number id="3DD924EF8020BC54DEDBFDE608EDFDAA" box="[390,449,610,634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="2007.0">2007</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C114D4B8020BC54DD0DFDE60BE8FDA9" box="[592,708,609,633]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="facialis">
<emphasis id="B965EADA8020BC54DD0DFDE60B4FFDA9" box="[592,611,610,633]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B965EADA8020BC54DD2CFDE50BE8FDA9" box="[625,708,609,633]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">facialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C114D4B8020BC54DDA6FDE60AA8FDA9" box="[763,900,610,633]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geminata">
<emphasis id="B965EADA8020BC54DDA6FDE60A22FDA9" box="[763,782,610,633]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B965EADA8020BC54DC41FDE60AA8FDA9" box="[796,900,610,633]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">geminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as two valid and distinct species. However, our examination of both primary 
<typeStatus id="54AA886A8020BC54DEB4FD020B08FD4E" box="[489,548,646,670]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">types</typeStatus>
concludes that they are, in fact, identical and have been newly synonymized here. The 
<typeStatus id="54AA886A8020BC54DE5AFD2D0845FD12" box="[263,361,681,706]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">holotype</typeStatus>
(not 
<typeStatus id="54AA886A8020BC54DEF9FD2E08D1FD12" box="[420,509,682,706]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">syntype</typeStatus>
) of 
<taxonomicName id="4C114D4B8020BC54DD77FD2E0BD7FD11" box="[554,763,681,705]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nitida" subSpecies="geminata">
<emphasis id="B965EADA8020BC54DD77FD2E0B11FD11" box="[554,573,682,705]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B965EADA8020BC54DD16FD2D0BD7FD11" box="[587,763,681,705]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">nitida geminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<collectionCode id="ED00AE0D8020BC54DC3FFD2E0A9BFD12" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" box="[866,951,682,706]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">USNM</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
